- Severe anaemia (Hb 2-6g/dL) with reduced MCV and MCH .
- Blood film (Fig.16.2) shows hypochromic microcytic cells, target cells, erythroblasts and, often, myelocytes.
- Bone marrow is hypercellular with erythroid hyperplasia.
- Globin chain synthesis studies show absent, or severely deficient, $\beta$-chain synthesis. Fetal haemoglobin variably increased.
