- Immunosuppression, e.g. antilymphocyte globulin (ALG), horse or rabbit, given intravenously over several days, corticosteroids and cyclosporin (alone or with ALG) improve marrow function in 50-70\% of severe cases.
- Androgens (e.g. oxymetholone) may benefit Fanconi's anaemia and acquired aplastic anaemia.
